snippet.textDisplay:
The place he is visiting is in between Daerim 1 dong and 2 dong. I do not suggest you people to visit this region around 9pm... because it is well known for frequent crimes occurring in this area.

How do I know this? Cause I live in the Daerim 2 dong. Yeah, the place became Chinarown and who knew our grandmother would be the last Korean to live Daerim dong XD. (She lived in 대림동 for over 45 years. And even before this place became Chinatown, it was a shady region, Where gang members meet and homeless used to live. While the homeless and gang members are gone now, I still see multiple Mahjong places operated. In Korea, gambling is illegal and any related activities to be hosted as addictive except for government approved areas. And the fact I saw at least 5 places usually operated under basement of residential units...
You get the point)
Be prepared when going to this region. Apologize quickly and act carefully. Cause there was an incident a person was stabbed to death by a stranger because he did not apologize after bumping into the stranger. If you don't know what you are doing in that region, maintain your walking speed with the locals.
Do be careful of food poisoning, because you will see some foods are displayed outside of a place they should not be. Honestly the only purpose of a person visiting here would be a) a person who wants to enjoy some Chinese food b) a person who wants to see architectural style of buildings in 70's.

snippet.textDisplay:
The third item ( the noodles) is super expensive for $5 usd!

My maternal side of family is from Shanghai, so we are picky on soup dumplings. I don’t know what to say, mike’s taste buds are very northern China. Shanghai people eat soup dumplings with ginger and vinegar. We don’t put chili oil on soup dumplings... it’s absurd... plus those dumplings’ wraps are so thick and the size is too big for a bite. There’s a reason we call it小籠包.
